.TH JTUTIL-VCD-COMPARE "1" "April 2026" "jtutil-vcd-compare manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-vcd-compare \- Compare two VCD databases
.SH DESCRIPTION
Load two VCD databases containing mostly identical scope and signals and
compare specific signals.
.PP
Not providing a signal name will compare all signals in the VCD
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil vcd compare file1[.vcd] file2[.vcd] [signal\-name] [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for compare
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-mismatch\fR int
stop at the given mismatch occurence (default 1)
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-rst\fR
ignore while any signal called rst is high
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-time\fR string
time at which comparison starts (scientific suffixes accepted) (default "0")
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-time_b\fR string
time at which comparison starts for the B (right) VCD. Same as \fB\-\-time\fR if \fB\-\-time_b\fR is ommitted (default "0")
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
verbose
